==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Doe
<hw>Doe</hw> <pr>(d⟦omac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>d⟦amac⟧</ets>; cf. Dan. <ets>daa</ets>, <ets>daa-</ets>dyr, deer,
and perh. L. <ets>dama</ets>. ⟦root⟧66.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
female deer or antelope; specifically, the female of the fallow deer, of
which the male is called a <xex>buck</xex>. Also applied to the female
of other animals, as the rabbit. See the Note under
<er>Buck</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doe</ent>⟦br⟧

